name: flask-babel
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "flask-babel" %}
{%set camelName = "Flask-Babel" %}
{%set version = "0.11.1" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash_val = "d29b36c399e42e98bc9401c8c1c159f2befcb8c12a2a2a87ec49ad7623036899" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ camelName }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - flask
    - babel >=2.3
    - jinja2 >=2.5

  run:
    - python
    - flask
    - babel >=2.3
    - jinja2 >=2.5

test:
  imports:
    - flask_babel

about:
  home: http://github.com/python-babel/flask-babel
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  summary: 'Adds i18n/l10n support to Flask applications'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
